  references historyedit after serving as cto for peregrine systems in san diego fred luddy started glidesoft inc in  glidesoft specialized in it service management applications based on itil standards in  the company changed its name to servicenow in  servicenow reported an annual revenue of  million and began serving it solutions to large companies such as tiaacref intel staples safeway university of san francisco and astrazeneca in  frank slootman replaced luddy as ceo slootman was previously the ceo of data domain before it was purchased by emc corporation in  servicenow became a publicly traded company servicenow was therefore the first technology company taken public by morgan stanley since facebook shortly after going public servicenow relocated its headquarters from san diego to santa clara servicenow currently holds additional office locations in san diego london new york city kirkland washington san francisco frankfurt orlando toronto sao paulo amsterdam paris singapore sydney and hyderabad on february   servicenow announced that its board of directors had named john donahoe president and ceo to start on april   when frank slootman the current president ceo and chairman of the board would be stepping down company timelineedit year month and date event  june  glidesoft inc incorporated in california  february  glidesoft inc changes name to servicenow  february  servicenow incorporated in delaware  june  servicenow becomes publicly traded company with an initial stock price of   april  servicenow receives federal information security management act moderate authority to operate ato from the united states general services administration this allows federal state and local government agencies to use the cloudbased servicenow software for it consolidation and service delivery as well as business process automation  july  servicenow acquires mirror  adding performance analytics to its cloudbased software  february  hewlettpackard files lawsuit against servicenow for infringing on eight patents the case was settled through a  fine to fred luddy  april  servicenow hosts the inaugural knowledge conference in san francisco entitled knowledge over  it professionals  large enterprise cios and  partners attended the event servicenow currently hosts a knowledge conference every year previously this conference had been held in las vegas servicenow has announced that the knowledge conference will be in orlando florida  july  servicenow acquires neebula systems israel for  million  september  bmc software inc sues servicenow for patent infringement  october  servicenow announces a  yearoveryear revenue growth  million  yearoveryear billings growth a  customer count and  renewal rate for its third financial quarter  february  servicenow acquires intréis inc for an undisclosed amount to accelerate its investment in enterprise governance risk and compliance grc solutions  april  servicenow announces the servicenow express program which provides cloudbased service management software for small and mediumsized enterprises  jan  servicenow announces total revenues of  billion for fiscal year   apr  servicenow pays  million to settle patent infringement litigation with bmc software and hewlett packard enterprise  jan  servicenow acquires dxcontinuum inc a silicon valley‑based machine‑learning company to embed its technology in the servicenow platform and across its products see alsoedit software industry in telangana referencesedit  glidesoft seeks san diego area businesses to participate in customer advisory program for innovative it service management solution press release glidesoft – via businesswire   executive team servicenow   service now now leading cloud provider passes with flying colors financialmarketswizardcom archived from the original on june     bigelow bruce v august   san diego’s servicenow driving hard as revenue soars expands to silicon valley xconomy   servicenow customers servicenow archived from the original on septem